26] Meanwhile, collectors are becoming more careful, discerning, and selective about their purchases.\", \"from\": 3317, \"to\": 3418, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"[Artnet Pro]  Worried that they would not have enough space to keep collecting, the Los Angeles-based coupleCandace and Charles Nelsonfound a two-fold solution to their problem.\", \"from\": 3418, \"to\": 3596, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3539, \"end\": 3546, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_I_of_England\", \"score\": 0.9973459652080402, \"rank\": 0.002364545920324503, \"text\": \"Charles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_I_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_I_of_England\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One, learn to appreciate smaller, more intimate works.\", \"from\": 3597, \"to\": 3651, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Two, team up with interior designerSara Storyto complete their modernist Beverly Hills home.\", \"from\": 3652, \"to\": 3744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3725, \"end\": 3738, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Real_Housewives_of_Beverly_Hills\", \"score\": 0.999999017240526, \"rank\": 9.827604870145997e-07, \"text\": \"Beverly Hills\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Real_Housewives_of_Beverly_Hills\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Real_Housewives_of_Beverly_Hills\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their walls boast works by contemporary artists with\\u00a0ties to California, including Ed Ruscha, Jonas Wood, and Brenna Youngblood.\", \"from\": 3745, \"to\": 3873, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3806, \"end\": 3816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.467220094994125e-15, \"text\": \"California\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California\"}, {\"begin\": 3828, \"end\": 3