\": \"One of the host city's selling points was that it would primarily rely on existing or temporary structures for sporting competitions, such as the Grand Palais for fencing and taekwondo, the Stade Roland-Garros for tennis and boxing, and the Stade de France, the country's national stadium, for athletics, rugby, and closing ceremonies.\", \"from\": 4707, \"to\": 5042, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Only the Aquatics Center in the suburb of Saint-Denis has been built specifically for the Games.\", \"from\": 5043, \"to\": 5139, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5085, \"end\": 5096, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Basilica_of_Saint-Denis\", \"score\": 0.9976073082181329, \"rank\": 0.002398418542950493, \"text\": \"Saint-Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Basilica_of_Saint-Denis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Basilica_of_Saint-Denis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The new permanent sports facility has been co-designed by the Amsterdam-based firm VenhoevenCS and the French architects Ateliers 2/3/4.\", \"from\": 5140, \"to\": 5276, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5243, \"end\": 5249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9231267114424365, \"rank\": 0.08322185025421802, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here is a glimpse of it.\", \"from\": 5277, \"to\": 5301, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"[AD]  The World's Premier Art Magazine since 1913.\", \"from\": 5301, \"to\": 5351, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Subscribe today and save!\", \"from\": 5352, \"to\": 5377, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sign Up for our Newsletters  Get our latest stories in the feed of your favorite networks  We want to hear from you!\", \"from\": 5379, \"to\": 5495, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Send us a tip using our anonymous form.\", \"from\": 5496, \"to\": 5535, \